Blocked on a gomc BUG in synchronized I/O (M67), localized 2026-07-11:
 - motion.analog-out-00 stays 0; the ngc uses `M67 E0 Q[#1]` (synchronized
   analog output) followed by three blended G1 moves per repeat iteration.
 - M67 and M68 both work via MDI, in AUTO with a single move, and in AUTO with
   a loop of single moves. It FAILS specifically when an M67 is followed by
   MULTIPLE continuously-blended moves in AUTO (empirically: 1 move -> works,
   3 blended moves -> output never applied).
 - The trajectory planner is NOT at fault: gomc src/emc/tp/tp.c syncdio
   attachment (tpSetupSyncedIO) and application (tpToggleDIOs / the parabolic
   blend toggle) are byte-identical to upstream 2.9, which handles this program
   correctly. So the bug is gomc-specific and upstream of the TP: milltask's
   (Go) canon-command streaming — the ordering/timing of SetAoutSyncCmd
   (-> motion set_aout -> tp->syncdio) relative to the move commands
   (-> add_line -> tpSetupSyncedIO consumes tp->syncdio) during AUTO read-ahead,
   so with multiple following moves the single tp->syncdio slot is mis-attached
   or overwritten before the intended move consumes it.
 - Fix target: src/gomc/internal/task canon queue / sequencer synchronized-I/O
   path. Remove this xfail once M67 synced output applies correctly with
   multiple blended moves.
